<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang='en'>
  <head>
    <meta charset='UTF-8'>
    <meta http-equiv='X-UA-Compatible' content='IE=edge'>
    <meta name='viewport' content='width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0'>
    <link rel='stylesheet' href='/style.css'>
    <title>Privacy Policy - Inclusion Bot</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class='container'>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <h2>How Inclusion Bot uses permissions</h2>
      <p>
        Inclusion Bot only requests Bot level Slack permissions, which means it has no authority to access detailed user information or perform actions on behalf of users.
      </p>
      <p>
        These are the specific permissions requested and how they are used:
      </p>
      
      <dl>
        <dt>channels:history</dt>
        <dd>To scan messages for non-inclusive languages if added to a channel</dd>
        
        <dt>groups:history</dt>
        <dd>To scan messages for non-inclusive languages if added to a channel</dd>
        
        <dt>mpim:history</dt>
        <dd>To scan messages for non-inclusive languages if added to a channel</dd>
        
        <dt>chat:write</dt>
        <dd>To reply to messages with inclusive alternatives</dd>        
      </dl>

      <h2>We will never:</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          Store or view any of your messages
        </li>
        <li>
          Store any personal information on our database regarding names, emails or other personal information
        </li>
      </ul>
      
      <h2>We only store:</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          Team or Enterprise ID
        </li>
        <li>
          Team or Enterprise Name
        </li>
        <li>
          Access tokens with relevant scopes
        </li>
        <li>
          User ID if a user has granted the app permission
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Website Data</h2>
      <p>
        The Inclusion Bot website does not collect any of your data.
      </p>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>